newsitem.title: AUSTRIA: Austria conservatives win most votes in Euro poll.
newsitem.headline: Austria conservatives win most votes in Euro poll.

text.p: Austria's conservative People's Party emerged as the strongest party in the country's first European parliament elections on Sunday, clinching 29.6 percent of the vote, final official results showed.

The Social Democrats of Chancellor Franz Vranitzky came second with 29.1 percent, while the far-right Freedom Party scored 27.6 percent. The leftist Green Party received 6.8 percent, and the Liberal Party 4.2, the Interior Ministry said in a statement.

The result gives the People's Party seven of Austria's 21 seats in the European Parliament. The SPOe and the FPOe get six seats each, while the Greens take one. The Liberals defied earlier projections by finally clinching one seat in the Strasbourg-based assembly.
Voter turnout was calculated at 67.21 percent of the 5.8 million Austrians who were eligible to vote in Sunday's poll.
